# BlackBar code owners.
#
# CODEOWNERS auto-requests review from the listed owners on every PR that
# touches the matching paths. Owners must be either users (e.g. `@octocat`)
# or teams scoped to the org (e.g. `@blackbar/maintainers`).
#
# TBD: the `@blackbar/maintainers` team does not exist yet — it will be
# created once the OSS migration completes and the `blackbar` GitHub org is
# spun up (audit Q1). Until then this file documents the intended ownership
# model but does not actually enforce reviews.

# Default — every path falls through to the maintainers team.
*                       @blackbar/maintainers

# Security-sensitive surfaces deserve a dedicated security review group once
# one exists. Until then they pile up under the same maintainers team.
/SECURITY.md            @blackbar/maintainers
/backend/src/auth/      @blackbar/maintainers
/backend/src/utils/audit_logger.py    @blackbar/maintainers

# CI + release tooling.
/.github/               @blackbar/maintainers
/docker-compose*.yml    @blackbar/maintainers
